text: It was very difficult to find what made a Zorb a Zorb.

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: Most Zorbs had spikes on their stems and dots on their leaves, but there were also some Zorbs that did not.

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: Colors did not seem to make a difference whether or not they were Zorbs.

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: The amount of curly ribbons coming out did not make a difference - some Zorbs had curly ribbons and some did not.

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems

text: Were there any other distinguishing marks or shapes?

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: What did the creatures look like overall?

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: They were flowers, some had curly ribbons coming out of them, some didn't have any ribbons.

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems
text: Were they all solitary or did some come in pairs?

rule_name: flowers with (thorns and purple petals) or orange stems

text: Any size differences?

text: Ollers have tail feathers (doesn't matter what color) and an orange wing.

rule_name: birds with orange wings and tails
